Subject: [PATCH 08/94] torque: filter fourth pass to Builtin declarables only

Task 1.6 landed the fourth pass as the plan specified, iterating every
declarable. Smoke-testing on the 245-file stock fileset under kCCBuiltins
SIGSEGVs: Visit(NamespaceConstant*) unconditionally drives CSAGenerator
and the assembler in a state that's only safe in the first (kCSA) pass,
and Visit(TorqueMacro)/Visit(Method) re-enter VisitMacroCommon which
runs the full inlining/assembler machinery even when streams are nulled.

The kCC and kCCDebug passes avoid this by iterating curated macro lists
(AllMacrosForCCOutput / AllMacrosForCCDebugOutput). The kCCBuiltins pass
has no analogous curated list yet, so we inline the filter in the loop:
only kBuiltin declarables produce output here. Phase 2 can widen this
if needed.

With the filter, torque exits 0 on the full stock fileset.
