From 446917043b683ba2b429f381e565f3cc505fc737 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Payton <brandon@happycode.net>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 19:32:29 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 48/94] torque: suppress CSA pass and drop inline for
 whitelisted JS-linkage builtins
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two fixes surfaced by Task 5.5's first full-host rebuild with a
JS-linkage fixture actually staged in the v8 tree:

1. CSA emission gate — for a whitelisted JS-linkage builtin the
   kCCBuiltins pass emits a real CPP(...) entry into BUILTIN_LIST_FROM_TORQUE
   (via Task 5.3's TFJ→CPP swap), which removes the `Generate_<Name>`
   declaration from builtins.h. The kCSA pass still unconditionally
   emitted `TF_BUILTIN(Name, CodeStubAssembler) { ... }` in the
   -tq-csa.cc, expanding to an out-of-line definition of the now-
   undeclared `Generate_<Name>`. Gate the kCSA emission on the same
   whitelist + IsJavaScript() check and emit a comment no-op instead.

2. External linkage — the CPP-ABI emission wrote `inline Address
   Builtin_<Name>(...)`. With no in-TU address-take, the compiler
   elided the out-of-line symbol under -O2, so mksnapshot's link
   against FUNCTION_ADDR(Builtin_<Name>) in builtins.cc's
   `builtin_metadata` table + the external-reference table failed with
   an undefined-symbol error. Drop `inline`; each builtin name is
   unique so external linkage has no ODR risk.

With both fixes in place, whitelisting TorqueCcTest_JsReturn links
mksnapshot + libv8_base_without_compiler.a + libv8_snapshot.a + d8 +
cctest cleanly, and `Builtin_TorqueCcTest_JsReturn` shows up as a
defined (T) symbol in libv8_base_without_compiler.a.

No effect on empty-whitelist output: both guards are scoped to
(whitelisted AND JS-linkage). Non-ccbuiltins torque sha stays at
2224e4db4e95629954def24da8660e7b3b3dd2f1.

Paired worktree commit adds test/torque-cc-fixtures/js-return.tq
to deps/v8/BUILD.gn and stages the fixture in-tree so torque actually
processes it during the V8 build.
---
 deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc | 23 +++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 22 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc b/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
index 0e94d80c..61299998 100644
--- a/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
+++ b/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
@@ -646,8 +646,14 @@ void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Builtin* builtin) {
       const std::string& name = builtin->ExternalName();
       const Signature& signature = builtin->signature();
 
+      // External linkage (no `inline`): V8 takes the address of
+      // Builtin_<Name> via FUNCTION_ADDR(...) in builtins.cc's
+      // `builtin_metadata` table and the external-reference table.
+      // Marking the definition `inline` without any in-TU address-take
+      // elides the symbol under -O2, breaking link. Each builtin name
+      // is unique, so external linkage has no ODR risk.
       csa_ccfile() << "// Builtin: " << name << "\n"
-                   << "inline Address Builtin_" << name
+                   << "Address Builtin_" << name
                    << "(int args_length, Address* args_object,\n"
                    << "                         Isolate* isolate) {\n"
                    << "  DCHECK(isolate->context().is_null() || "
@@ -838,6 +844,21 @@ void ImplementationVisitor::Visit(Builtin* builtin) {
     cc_builtin_entries_.push_back(std::move(entry));
     return;
   }
+  // kCSA output: for whitelisted JS-linkage builtins, the CPP-ABI
+  // emission in -tq-ccbuiltins.cc fully replaces the TFJ CSA emission,
+  // and builtin-definitions.h carries `CPP(Name, ...)` rather than
+  // `TFJ(Name, ...)`. Skip TF_BUILTIN here so the CSA .cc does not
+  // reference `Generate_<Name>`, which is no longer declared.
+  {
+    const auto& whitelist = GlobalContext::cc_builtins_whitelist();
+    if (builtin->IsJavaScript() &&
+        whitelist.find(builtin->ExternalName()) != whitelist.end()) {
+      csa_ccfile() << "// Builtin: " << builtin->ExternalName()
+                   << " (CSA emission suppressed — whitelisted JS-linkage "
+                   << "builtin, see -tq-ccbuiltins.cc)\n\n";
+      return;
+    }
+  }
   CurrentScope::Scope current_scope(builtin);
   CurrentCallable::Scope current_callable(builtin);
   CurrentReturnValue::Scope current_return_value;
