Subject: [PATCH 70/94] runtime-macro-shims: add IsSafeInteger for
 NumberIsSafeInteger
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Surfaced by whitelisting NumberIsSafeInteger in kCCBuiltins. One new
shim:

  IsSafeInteger(Tagged<Object>) -> bool  (cast.tq:10)

Spec: value is an integer AND |value| <= 2^53 - 1 (= MAX_SAFE_INTEGER).
All Smis are safe (Smi range on 64-bit host is within [-2^53, 2^53]);
HeapNumber needs the absolute-value bound after the integer check.

NumberIsSafeInteger's body is otherwise identical in shape to
NumberIsInteger — one-liner lowering to IsSafeInteger + SelectBooleanConstant.
SelectBooleanConstant was added in Task 6.5.

No emitter changes required.
---
 deps/v8/src/torque/runtime-macro-shims.h | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)

diff --git a/deps/v8/src/torque/runtime-macro-shims.h b/deps/v8/src/torque/runtime-macro-shims.h
index 0243735c..6b54d452 100644
--- a/deps/v8/src/torque/runtime-macro-shims.h
+++ b/deps/v8/src/torque/runtime-macro-shims.h
@@ -125,6 +125,23 @@ inline Tagged<Boolean> SelectBooleanConstant(bool b) {
            : Cast<Boolean>(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).false_value());
 }
 
+// Phase 6 Task 6.6 — shim added for NumberIsSafeInteger whitelist.
+// Declared `extern macro IsSafeInteger(Object): bool;` in cast.tq:10.
+// Spec: v is an integer and |v| <= 2^53 - 1 (= Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER).
+// All Smis are safe (Smi range on 64-bit is [-2^31, 2^31-1]); HeapNumber
+// values need the absolute-value bound check after the integer check.
+inline bool IsSafeInteger(Tagged<Object> v) {
+  if (IsSmi(v)) return true;
+  if (IsHeapNumber(v)) {
+    double d = Cast<HeapNumber>(v)->value();
+    if (std::isnan(d) || std::isinf(d)) return false;
+    if (std::floor(d) != d) return false;
+    // 2^53 - 1 = 9007199254740991.0 (Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER).
+    return std::abs(d) <= 9007199254740991.0;
+  }
+  return false;
+}
+
 }  // namespace CodeStubAssembler
 }  // namespace TorqueRuntimeMacroShims
 }  // namespace internal
