Phase 6.1 cleanup (I-1 follow-up from Phase 6 code review). The
Phase-6 approach emitted `True_0(Isolate::Current())` and
`False_0(Isolate::Current())` at every NamespaceConstant call site.
The helper functions took an Isolate* parameter and forwarded it to
ReadOnlyRoots(). Each NumberIs* invocation therefore made one TLS read
per true/false-returning path at the emission site.

Change: both helpers become zero-arg inline functions that acquire
the isolate via Isolate::Current() internally. The CCGenerator's
NamespaceConstant emission under kCCBuiltins now writes `True_0()` /
`False_0()` — no isolate token at the call site. Stock kCC / kCCDebug
passes still emit `<const>(isolate)` (unchanged gating).

Call-site token count drops from O(N × 2 × len("Isolate::Current()"))
to O(N × 2 × 0), and the TLS-fetch knowledge is consolidated in one
place. The `Isolate::Current()` DCHECK that was already holding at
every call site continues to hold (JS execution has a current isolate
by definition).

