MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three trivial Phase-8 shims for the lowering of `tail Add(n, 1)` in
`Increment`. The torque emitter produces:

  tmp4 = TqRuntimeFromConstexpr_Number_constexpr_IntegerLiteral_0(IntegerLiteral(false, 0x1ull));
  return Builtin_Add(isolate, parameter0, tmp1, tmp4);

…and `TqRuntimeFromConstexpr_Number…IntegerLiteral_0` itself lowers
to `NumberConstant((ConstexprIntegerLiteralToFloat64(p_i)))`.
`SmiFromUint32` is hit by the BigInt arm’s `SmiTag<Operation>`.
