Phase 8 prerequisite: helper bodies emitted via EnsureInCCBuiltinsOutputList
do NOT have an `Isolate*` parameter, but the prior CallBuiltin emission
spelled `isolate` literally — so any helper that called another builtin
failed to compile (`use of undeclared identifier 'isolate'`). Mirrors
Phase 6.1's I-1 pattern: under kCCBuiltins, the TLS read via
`Isolate::Current()` resolves to the same value the outer builtin's
`Isolate*` parameter holds. Cost: single-digit-ns extra TLS read per
CallBuiltin in kCCBuiltins emission. The non-kCCBuiltins (kCSA/kCC)
path still uses literal `isolate` — no behaviour change there.

Affects both branches of CCGenerator::EmitInstruction(CallBuiltin):
- tail-call (Phase 7, line 539-540): `return Builtin_<X>(Isolate::Current(), ...)`
- non-tail (Phase 2, line 570): `<result> = Builtin_<X>(Isolate::Current(), ...)`

Concretely unblocks Increment: TqRuntimeUnaryOp1_0's body calls
Builtin_NonNumberToNumeric(isolate, …) at the JSAnyNotNumeric arm,
which now resolves cleanly when emitted into a kCCBuiltins TU.
