MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Including `heap/factory.h` and `numbers/conversions-inl.h` from
runtime-macro-shims.h transitively pulls descriptor-array-tq-inl.inc
into compilation contexts where TorqueRuntimeMacroShims::CodeStubAssembler
hasn't yet been opened (e.g., the v8_compiler chain via
fixed-array-inl.h → runtime-macro-shims.h → conversions-inl.h →
heap-number-inl.h → primitive-heap-object-inl.h → … →
descriptor-array-inl.h → descriptor-array-tq-inl.inc), causing 'unknown
type name IntegerLiteral' / 'use of undeclared identifier
TorqueRuntimeMacroShims' across ~1000 .o targets.

Fix: drop the new heavy includes from the shims header, move
`NumberConstant` to implementation-visitor.cc's per-kCCBuiltins-.cc
preamble where factory-inl.h and conversions-inl.h are reachable
(every kCCBuiltins .cc already includes them as part of the standard
preamble). Lives inside namespace TorqueRuntimeMacroShims::
CodeStubAssembler so the emitter's qualified emission
`TorqueRuntimeMacroShims::CodeStubAssembler::NumberConstant(...)`
resolves at the call site.

The remaining shims (IsBigInt, ConstexprIntegerLiteralToFloat64,
SmiFromUint32) only need the existing minimum include set, so they
stay in the header.
