Phase 8.1 quick win: Decrement's torque body (`tail Subtract(n, 1)`)
hits the same TFC C-symbol-absence as Increment did at Phase 7A. The
fix is structurally identical to Phase 8's Builtin_Add — emit an
inline Builtin_Subtract(Isolate*, Context, Number, Number) → Number
in the kCCBuiltins .cc preamble next to Builtin_Add. Same Smi/HeapNumber
logic, just `l - r` instead of `l + r`.

Covers the Number(Number, Number) overload at number.tq:373. Full
ECMA Subtract is unaffected (still in CSA-emitted Code object).
Pattern is now demonstrated as repeatable: each TFC tail-call target
costs ~30 LoC of preamble bridge.
---
 deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc | 33 ++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 33 insertions(+)

diff --git a/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc b/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
index 521fadb7..924ddeff 100644
--- a/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
+++ b/deps/v8/src/torque/implementation-visitor.cc
@@ -2309,6 +2309,39 @@ void ImplementationVisitor::GenerateImplementation(const std::string& dir) {
         "  return Cast<Number>(*isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(sum));\n"
         "}\n"
         "\n"
+        "// `Builtin_Subtract` mirrors `Builtin_Add` for the Number(Number,\n"
+        "// Number) → Number overload at number.tq:373 — the path Decrement's\n"
+        "// `tail Subtract(n, 1)` hits. Same Smi/HeapNumber logic as Add,\n"
+        "// just with `l - r` instead of `l + r`.\n"
+        "inline Tagged<Number> Builtin_Subtract(Isolate* isolate,\n"
+        "                                       Tagged<Context> context,\n"
+        "                                       Tagged<Number> left,\n"
+        "                                       Tagged<Number> right) {\n"
+        "  USE(context);\n"
+        "  if (IsSmi(left) && IsSmi(right)) {\n"
+        "    int64_t l = static_cast<int64_t>(Cast<Smi>(left).value());\n"
+        "    int64_t r = static_cast<int64_t>(Cast<Smi>(right).value());\n"
+        "    int64_t diff = l - r;\n"
+        "    if (Smi::IsValid(diff)) {\n"
+        "      return Cast<Number>(Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(diff)));\n"
+        "    }\n"
+        "    return Cast<Number>(\n"
+        "        *isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(static_cast<double>(diff)));\n"
+        "  }\n"
+        "  double l = IsSmi(left)\n"
+        "      ? static_cast<double>(Cast<Smi>(left).value())\n"
+        "      : Cast<HeapNumber>(left)->value();\n"
+        "  double r = IsSmi(right)\n"
+        "      ? static_cast<double>(Cast<Smi>(right).value())\n"
+        "      : Cast<HeapNumber>(right)->value();\n"
+        "  double diff = l - r;\n"
+        "  int smi_value;\n"
+        "  if (DoubleToSmiInteger(diff, &smi_value)) {\n"
+        "    return Cast<Number>(Smi::FromInt(smi_value));\n"
+        "  }\n"
+        "  return Cast<Number>(*isolate->factory()->NewHeapNumber(diff));\n"
+        "}\n"
+        "\n"
         "// `Builtin_NonNumberToNumeric` wraps Object::ToNumeric, which\n"
         "// implements ECMAScript ToNumeric (string parse, boolean→Smi,\n"
         "// null/undefined coercion, ToPrimitive recurse). Symbol inputs\n"
