Phase 9A.2's emitter landed the catch_block dispatch but missed three
follow-on pieces that surfaced when the catch-block fixture was first
fully compiled (cctest TU pulls -tq-ccbuiltins.cc into v8_base):

1. cc-generator.cc: EmitCatchBlockDispatch declared the exception
   variable as Tagged<Object>, but the catch block's phi input
   expects Tagged<JSAny> (CSA's csa-generator.cc:686 declares
   TNode<JSAny>). isolate->exception() returns Tagged<Object>, so
   we now UncheckedCast<JSAny> on the assignment. Fixes 'no viable
   overloaded =' compile errors at every catch dispatch site.

2. runtime-macro-shims.h: + SmiNotEqual, SmiConstant — emitted by
   torque for in-try Smi comparisons and integer-literal Smi
   construction.

3. implementation-visitor.cc preamble: + StringConstant (interns C
   string literal as v8 String via Factory), GetPendingMessage /
   SetPendingMessage (access the isolate's pending-message slot
   used by TqRuntimeGetAndResetPendingMessage_0 in the catch flow),
   TheHole_0 (NamespaceConstant pattern parallel to True_0/False_0,
   used to clear the pending-message slot), Undefined_0 (same
   pattern, used by callers passing Undefined as JSAny).

4. test/torque-cc-fixtures/catch-block.tq: switch from a custom
   runtime::ThrowTypeError decl + SmiConstant(0)+'forced' to the
   already-declared ThrowCalledNonCallable(Undefined). Avoids a
   MessageTemplate-arity mismatch (kNoMessage expects 0 args; we
   were passing 1) that aborted the runtime call's MessageFormatter
   at test time, and removes the local extern decl boilerplate.
