From 862bd78e2764ddf17d8bd137199030f0815eb4f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brandon Payton <brandon@happycode.net>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 02:24:55 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 94/94] torque: kCCBuiltins lifts StoreReference non-smi-tagged
 emission gate
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 10 close. Phase 5 lifted LoadReference's non-smi-tagged gate via
is_cc_builtins_; this is the symmetric lift for StoreReference.

The TaggedField<T>::store(host, offset, value) emission below the gate
(cc-generator.cc:1067-1069) was already correct — V8's 3-arg overload
needs no PtrComprCageBase (stores compress, not decompress). Only the
conservative Error() guard at line 1057-1061 needed lifting for
kCCBuiltins. kCSA and kCC paths stay byte-identical.

This unblocks `new T{...}` allocation lowering (NewFixedArray,
NewJSArray, etc.) for any kCCBuiltins-whitelisted target. Phase 9B's
catch-block + varargs synthetic targets do not exercise this path,
so cctest fixtures stay byte-exact (verified via run-torque-fixtures.sh
post-rebuild — all 18 goldens unchanged). The PromiseTry forcing
target that would exercise it is deferred to Phase 11 along with the
broader struct/tuple emitter reconciliation discovered during Task
10.0 v2 triage.

Verification:
- 18/18 fixtures byte-exact (no golden refresh needed).
- 16/16 cctests pass.
- 26/26 d8-smoke probes pass.
- 2/2 mjsunit files pass.
- Excluding-anchor 8169724e stable (number/tail-call/catch-block/js-varargs excluded).
- All 5 wasm-posix-kernel suites 0 delta vs Phase 9.7 baseline.
---
 deps/v8/src/torque/cc-generator.cc | 13 +++++++++----
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/deps/v8/src/torque/cc-generator.cc b/deps/v8/src/torque/cc-generator.cc
index 6b7c9c05..1024a2c9 100644
--- a/deps/v8/src/torque/cc-generator.cc
+++ b/deps/v8/src/torque/cc-generator.cc
@@ -1051,10 +1051,15 @@ void CCGenerator::EmitInstruction(const StoreReferenceInstruction& instruction,
   // store variants.
   std::string result_type = instruction.type->GetRuntimeType();
   if (instruction.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetTaggedType())) {
-    // Symmetric with LoadReference: only smi tagged values are handled today;
-    // plumb PtrComprCageBase through generated code once we need to store
-    // HeapObject-typed fields.
-    if (!instruction.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType())) {
+    // Stores on non-smi tagged fields use TaggedField<T>::store(host, offset,
+    // value) — the 3-arg overload that needs no cage_base (stores compress, not
+    // decompress). Symmetric with LoadReference's `is_cc_builtins_` gate at the
+    // non-smi tagged path: kCSA/kCC stock kept the conservative error to avoid
+    // exercising untested codegen surface; kCCBuiltins needs the path live for
+    // `new T{...}` allocation lowering (NewFixedArray / NewJSArray, reached
+    // transitively from PromiseTry's NewRestArgumentsFromArguments).
+    if (!is_cc_builtins_ &&
+        !instruction.type->IsSubtypeOf(TypeOracle::GetSmiType())) {
       Error(
           "Not supported in C++ output: StoreReference on non-smi tagged "
           "value");
